sequenceDiagram
    participant SNAP as SnapshotCoordinator
    participant WM as WatermarkWriter
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant SR as SnapshotReader
    participant WAL as WAL Stream
    participant REC as ReconciliationEngine
    participant DEL as DeliveryCoordinator

    SNAP->>WM: writeLowWatermark(windowId)
    WM->>PG: UPDATE cdc_control.watermark SET value = lowUUID
    SNAP->>SR: readChunk(table, keyRange, chunkSize)
    SR->>PG: SELECT * FROM table WHERE pk > lastPk ORDER BY pk LIMIT n
    PG-->>SR: chunk rows (READ COMMITTED)
    SNAP->>WM: writeHighWatermark(windowId)
    WM->>PG: UPDATE cdc_control.watermark SET value = highUUID

    WAL-->>REC: low watermark event observed in WAL
    Note over REC: Enter window mode — buffer log events
    WAL-->>REC: log events between low and high watermark
    REC->>REC: remove matching primary keys from chunk rows
    WAL-->>REC: high watermark event observed in WAL
    Note over REC: Window closed — emit merged output

    REC-->>DEL: log events in window order
    REC-->>DEL: surviving snapshot rows (no key collision)
    DEL->>DEL: publish batch and advance WAL checkpoint
